**PAGE 4 — PROJECT WORKSPACE**
Route: `/dashboard/project/:id`

The most complex page. Three distinct phases depending on project state.

On load: reads the project record, its JD audit output, ghost candidate profile, all candidates with their scores and status, and the pool health report if complete.

Phase 1 — JD not uploaded yet. The page shows a large upload zone occupying most of the screen. Paste or file upload. Prominent. Nothing else competes for attention. On submit, the JD audit runs in background. The page transitions to a loading state showing real-time audit progress — what the system is currently doing, in plain language. When the audit completes, the page re-renders to show the JD audit output and the ghost candidate profile side by side. The recruiter can review and edit must-haves before proceeding. An edit here affects the ghost candidate and insider signal checklist.

Phase 2 — JD analyzed, candidates not yet uploaded. The JD audit output is now a collapsed panel at the top — still readable but not dominant. Center of the page is a drag and drop zone for bulk resume upload. The ghost candidate profile card sits in a sidebar. As files are dropped, a file list appears with upload progress per file. Once uploaded, analysis starts automatically.

Phase 3 — Analysis running or complete. This is the primary state the page lives in.

Top band: Pool Health Report. Full width, dark navy background. The numbers that matter most — total applicants, actually qualified, average inflation, hidden gems found, honest candidate rate. These numbers update as analysis completes. If analysis is still running, some of these are partial — they show what's known so far with a note that they'll update.

Below that: weight slider panel. Collapsed by default, expandable. Five sliders, one per scoring dimension. They must sum to 100 — the UI enforces this with normalization. Preset buttons: Founding Engineer, Senior IC, Compliance Role, Growth Hire. Changing any slider re-ranks the candidate list instantly — no API call, pure client-side math using the already-loaded scores.

Below that: ranked candidate list. Cards in a two-column grid. Each card shows rank, name, final score, trajectory label, ghost match score, red flags in plain English, and one line of system narrative — what the resume says versus what the system found. Cards that are still analyzing show the scanner shimmer animation. Cards complete show full output.

Clicking a candidate card goes to `/project/:id/candidate/:cid`.

Export button: top right. Downloads CSV with all scores, flags, questions, narratives for every analyzed candidate.

View Pool Intelligence: link to `/project/:id/pool`.

Real-time behavior: as workers complete candidates during analysis, the list updates. New cards appear in ranked position — not appended to the bottom. The list continuously re-sorts itself as more candidates complete. This is powered by Supabase Realtime watching the candidates table for this project.

