**PAGE 6 — POOL INTELLIGENCE**
Route: `/dashboard /project/:id/pool`

The meta-report. What the system found about the entire applicant pool — not any individual.

On load: reads the pool_health_report record for this project. Single read. This report is generated once when all candidates complete and stored — it does not recalculate on every page view.

What it shows:

Full-width stat band at the top: total applicants, actually qualified count and percentage, average inflation rate across the pool, most over-claimed skill with evidence, most under-claimed skill, hidden gems count, honest candidate rate.

Distribution charts: score distribution histogram — how the pool clusters. Trajectory distribution — how many Accelerating versus Steady versus Plateaued versus Declining. Inflation distribution — how many low, medium, high inflation candidates.

Hidden gems section: specific candidates who scored low on surface signals but high on insider signals. Named. Linked. The recruiter can click directly to their detail page.

JD warnings: specific language in the job description that is attracting the wrong candidates. The exact sentences from the JD that are causing keyword-matchers to apply. Specific rewrite suggestions.

Market signal: a paragraph the system generates about what this pool says about the talent market for this role right now. Not opinion — observation from the data. "68% of applicants claim ML as a core skill. 11% show evidence consistent with that claim. Either the market is oversaturated with surface-level ML candidates, or the JD language is too generic to filter them."

Pool narrative: a full paragraph summary of what the recruiter should take away from this pool before making any decisions.

Download: one button. Full pool intelligence report as PDF, not just CSV.

