**PAGE 8 — SETTINGS: API KEYS**
Route: `/settings/api-keys`

The BYOK management screen.

On load: reads all api_keys records for this org — provider, model, masked key (last 4 chars only), label, status, last used timestamp, last validated timestamp.

What it shows: a list of all connected keys. Each key row shows status dot (blue active, gray inactive, red error), provider icon plus model name, masked key, user label, last used relative time, action buttons — Test, Deactivate, Delete.

Add key flow: button opens a modal. Provider select, model select, key input (masked), label input. On submit: backend validates the key with a live test call. If validation passes, key is encrypted and stored, row appears in the list with active status. If validation fails, specific error shown — never stored.

Test button: sends a fresh validation call against the stored encrypted key. Updates the last validated timestamp. Shows pass or fail with specific reason.

Cost estimate panel: below the key list. Shows estimated cost per candidate analysis for each active key based on the provider's current token pricing. Updates if the model selection changes.

Model switching: each key row has an inline model selector. Changing it writes immediately to the database. Future analyses using this key will use the new model.

---

**PAGE 9 — SETTINGS: TEAM**
Route: `/settings/team`

Reads: all org_members records for this org — name, email, role, joined date, last active.

Shows: member list table. Each row: avatar initial, name, email, role badge (Owner / Admin / Recruiter / Viewer), joined date, last active relative time, actions (change role, remove — disabled for Owner row).

Invite flow: button opens a modal. Email input, role select. On submit: creates a pending invite record, sends email with signed invite link that expires in 48 hours. Pending invites appear in a separate section below the active members list with a Resend and Cancel option.

Role change: inline dropdown on each row. Writes immediately. Role changes take effect on the next request the affected user makes — their JWT is not invalidated but the DB RLS check picks up the new role.

Remove member: confirmation modal. Writes deletion to org_members. Does not delete their user account — just removes org access.

---

**PAGE 10 — SETTINGS: BILLING**
Route: `/settings/billing`

Reads: current plan, billing cycle, candidate usage this month versus limit, project count, user count, invoice history.

Shows: current plan card with usage meters. Candidates used this month as a progress bar with number. Projects count. Users count. Each meter turns amber at 80% and red at 95%.

Upgrade flow: plan comparison table inline on the page. Select a higher plan, confirm, redirects to payment. Downgrade shows a warning about which features will be lost and which data will be affected.

Invoice history: table of past invoices with date, amount, plan, status, download PDF link.

BYOK note: persistent reminder that LLM costs are separate and go directly to the user's provider account. Links to the API keys page.

---

**PAGE 11 — SETTINGS: SECURITY**
Route: `/settings/security`

Reads: all active sessions for this user, full audit log for this org.

Sessions section: list of all active login sessions — device type, browser, IP address (hashed and masked), location approximation, last active time, current session highlighted. Force logout button on each non-current session. Force logout all other sessions button at the top.

Password change: current password, new password, confirm. Writes to Supabase Auth.

Two-factor auth: toggle. If enabled, shows QR code for authenticator app setup. If already enabled, shows backup codes and a disable option.

Audit log: paginated table. Every action that touched data in this org. Timestamp, user who did it, action type, what resource was affected. Filterable by user, by action type, by date range. Exportable as JSON or CSV. Retained for 24 months.

This page exists because of GDPR Article 30 and the EU AI Act audit requirements. It is not decorative. It is the compliance paper trail.